  <title>WebKit2.WebView::ready-to-show</title>
  <synopsis><code mime="text/x-gjs">
connect('ready-to-show', function (webView, ): void);
  </code></synopsis>
  <p>Emitted after <link xref="WebKit2.WebView-create"/> on the newly created <link xref="WebKit2.WebView"/>
when it should be displayed to the user. When this signal is emitted
all the information about how the window should look, including
size, position, whether the location, status and scrollbars
should be displayed, is already set on the <link xref="WebKit2.WindowProperties"/>
of @web_view. See also <link xref="WebKit2.WebView.get_window_properties"/>.</p>

<terms>
<item>
<title><code>webView</code></title>
<p>instance of <link xref="WebKit2.WebView"/> that is emitting the signal</p>
